    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Glow Plug Sleeve Replacement</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, wear safety glasses with side shields whenever
                    using compressed air for cleaning purposes. Limit the air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi). See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                </para>
            </warning>
            <note>
                <para>Be certain that the glow plug recess was cleaned out with the Glow Plug Sleeve Brush, and rinsed
                    with a suitable cleaning solution and blown out with shop air.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e300575" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0862.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Applying Loctite&#174; #620 sealant to sleeve locations</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wall (end)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Upper wall (top)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite&#174; #620 sealant to the wall and upper wall on the glow plug sleeve. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_116.xml" xrefid="E30005C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300576" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0863.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Installing the glow plug sleeve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow Plug Sleeve Installer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow plug sleeve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="e300577" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD08/D08138.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing glow plug sleeve into place</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow plug installation tool</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow plug sleeve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install glow plug sleeve in cylinder head with the Glow Plug Sleeve Installer. Continue to
                tap the installer until the sleeve bottoms. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_116.xml" xrefid="E30005C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean glow plug sleeve after installation with a nylon brush and solvent. Make sure Loctite&#174;
                sealant is cleaned out before it hardens.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
